comment:
* Fast case mapping data for ASCII/Latin.
     * Linear arrays of delta bytes: 0=no mapping; EXC=exception.
     * Deltas must not cross the ASCII boundary, or else they cannot be easily used
     * in simple UTF-8 code.

variables.name: LIMIT
variables.comment: Case mapping/folding data for code points up to U+017F.

variables.name: LONG_S
variables.comment: U+017F case-folds and uppercases crossing the ASCII boundary.

variables.name: EXC
variables.comment: Exception: Complex mapping, or too-large delta.

variables.name: TO_LOWER_NORMAL
variables.comment: Deltas for lowercasing for most locales, and default case folding.

variables.name: TO_LOWER_TR_LT
variables.comment: Deltas for lowercasing for tr/az/lt, and Turkic case folding.

variables.name: TO_UPPER_NORMAL
variables.comment: Deltas for uppercasing for most locales.
